Functionality
- Does the software design implement the specifications and requirements? 
- Are the specifications and requirements complete for the users?
- Is the design functionality consistent?
Performance
- Does the design represent works for the all specified operating environment?
  - Windows?
  - MAC?
  - Linux?
- Does the software run without error?
- Are the primary performance requirements specified?
- Are the performance requirements such as being able to operate on the minimum hardware requirements met (2Hz cpu, 1GB RAM)?
Interface
- Does the interface facilitates troubleshooting?
- Do all the interfaces provide the required information?
- Are all the interfaces consistent with the requirements?
- Is the interface appealing to look at?
- Is the interface easy to navigate?
- Are all buttons and other inputs clear and unambiguous?
- Are all text and labels clear and unambiguous?
Data Usage
- Is there any data structure needed that has not been defined?
- Are all objects, relationships, and parameter documented?
Logic
- Are all the actions taken correctly in all cases?
Testability
- Can the software programs be tested in an incremental manner?
- Can the module that this design describes be tested or inspected to show that it satisfies the requirements?
- Is the software thoroughly tested?
Documentation
- Is the software well documented?
- Is the installation well documented?
